value:
Should I raise my blade to you in
a fit of frenzy, you must not hesitate.
Not even for a moment.

Alfonse and Sharena are not yet
prepared to usher in Askr's future...
And I laid that burden upon them.

Henriette, never lose that radiant
smile. Walk toward the light, the
people of Askr beside you.

This body of mine is not of the living.
It has no place beside those who yet
draw breath.

I am merely of the endless cohort of
the dead—one of the innumerable
victims of conflict.

Fear not. Your friend is safe. The
grasp of Hel has not yet closed...
as it has upon my throat.

When will you let me die? How much
more blood must stain these hands?

The dead have no need of power.
Yet here I stand.

This body is not fit to persist amongst
the living. It should decay...

You need not concern yourself with
me. Your gifts are wasted on a corpse.

I am Gustav. Once I was king, but no
more. I am but a king's rotting husk.

I have a request for you—not as a
king, but as a father who dearly
loves his children.$k$pWhen all of this is over, I hope that
you will grant me the eternal rest
that I have been denied.$k$pAt that time...bury my axe on the
hill that overlooks the castle of
Askr.$k$pThat way, at least some part of me
will be able to stand watch over them
as time marches ever onward.$k$pThe dead ought not to trouble the
living. Summoner... I leave Alfonse
and Sharena in your capable hands.
でぇい！
効かぬ！
ぐう…
Good...
Strike me.
You must understand.
Not good enough, I'm afraid.
Give it your all!
Well done...
Heavy sigh...
I am Gustav. My flesh has been reconstructed by the dread power of Hel.
Do not approach me. I can make no promises for your safety.
My body is beyond even my control.
One who lacks the will to strike me down is not fit to be king.
Alfonse is strong... If the time comes that he must battle his own blood, he will not falter.
Alfonse... Sharena... My beloved children.
As I am now, I can do no more than entrust my fate to you.
Yes.
And now?
Consider it done.
